\section{Philosophical Reflections: Realism and Non-locality}
\label{sec:philosophy}

As beautifully articulated in the video walkthrough\cite{youtube_bell2025}, Bell's theorem forces us to confront uncomfortable philosophical choices. The three assumptions underlying Bell's proof are:
\begin{itemize}
\item \textbf{Locality:} The measurement result at detector A should not depend on the setting at distant detector B
\item \textbf{Realism:} Physical properties exist independently of measurement
\item \textbf{Freedom of choice:} Experimenters can freely choose measurement settings
\end{itemize}

Quantum mechanics violates Bell inequalities, forcing us to abandon at least one assumption.

